AGI -&nbsp; Foreign Minister, Antonio Tajani, welcomed the Air Force C-130J aircraft in Ciampino with 15 Palestinian minors coming from the Gaza Strip, for most cancer patients.
&nbsp;
"This is an extraordinary result obtained by the Italian government. They are the first children with cancer who receive such assistance", said the owner of the Farnesina at the press point set up on the track of Stormo 31, underlining the success of the operation thanks to the joint work of civil protection, armed forces, consulated in Jerusalem and embassy in Tel Aviv: "Everyone has worked in synergy, no one has pulled back, everyone has tried to give the most to help these children."
<div </div
After visiting and bringing a greeting to children on the C-130J, Tajani, with few words broken by emotion, described to journalists the difficult condition of health of children, ensuring that "they will be greeted with open arms like the many other children we have received, sick or injured, in the previous operations", but above all that they will be treated "in the best hospitals of Italy".
&nbsp;
On the track to wait for the flight even seven outpatients ready to transport patients immediately to the Umberto I Polyclinic, where a medical-sanitary team awaits them for the first reception.<br> The Minister of the University Anna Maria Bernini, the director of the Sapienza University of Rome Antonella Polimeni and the Egyptian Franciscan, Father Ibrahim Faltas, who has lived in Palestine for 36 years and represents one of the main contacts of Italy with the Palestinian world.
&nbsp;
The health evacuations of Palestinian children from Gaza are included in the framework of humanitarian aid that the Italian Government initiated after the outbreak of the war in Gaza on 7 October 2023. Today's welcome is part of the project "Food for Gaza" launched on 11 March 2024 and that last 6 February saw the Foreign Minister deliver to Ashdod, Israel, tons of aid to the population. &nbsp;
